Application StressWatch is designed around privacy. We hope you will find this privacy policy clear and transparent. Do not hesitate to contact us at hi@stresswatch.app if you have any questions.
Apple Health Data: The health data we access from Apple Health is used solely for the purpose of analyzing your stress status. This includes providing insights, trends, and recommendations based on the data locally on your device. Your health data are stored only locally on your device and all calculations are done on your device as well.
Sign-In Information: Your Apple ID sign-in information is used to authenticate your identity and ensure secure access to your StressWatch account. We do not store any personally identifiable information related to your Apple ID.
The application collects some usage data that are essential for us to deliver our services, to understand your needs and to improve our services. The analytics services automatically collect certain information that does not personally identify our end users who access or use our mobile applications. This information includes but is not limited to device state information, unique device identifiers, installation UUID, device hardware and OS information, information relating to how application functions or anonymized IP addresses.
The application does NOT collect any personal data that directly identifies you such as your name, surname, email or anything you type within the app.
You can optionally backup your data using iCloud Drive. iCloud secures your information by encrypting it when it's in transit, storing it in iCloud in an encrypted format, and using secure tokens for authentication. For certain sensitive information, Apple uses end-to-end encryption. This means that only you can access your information, and only on devices where you're signed into iCloud. No one else, not even Apple, can access end-to-end encrypted information. You can read more about iCloud security overview here:
https://support.apple.com/en-us/HT202303
Apple Health Data:
We do not store any Apple Health data on StressWatch servers. All health data remains on your device and is processed locally. StressWatch never shares any health data with any third party services.
Security Measures:
We implement appropriate technical and organizational measures to protect your data from unauthorized access, loss, misuse, or alteration.
Access and Control: You have the right to access and control your personal information. You can manage the health data shared with StressWatch via the Apple Health app settings on your device.
Account Deletion: If you choose to delete your StressWatch account, your sign-in information and any associated data will be permanently deleted.
StressWatch is committed to protecting your privacy and ensuring that your data is handled securely and transparently. In addition to our own privacy practices, StressWatch complies with the privacy policies and guidelines set forth by Meta when integrating with their platform.
We also adhere to all applicable privacy laws and regulations, including but not limited to:
General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR):
For users in the European Union, we ensure that your data is processed lawfully, transparently, and for legitimate purposes.
California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA):
For users in California, we provide clear options to access, delete, and control your personal data.
Key Practices:
Data collected through StressWatch is only used for the purposes outlined in this policy and is never shared with third parties without your consent.
When using Meta services, such as logging in via Facebook, any data exchanged complies with Meta's privacy policy.
You retain full rights to request access to, correction of, or deletion of your data at any time.
We reserve the right, at our sole discretion, to modify or replace this Policy at any time. Any changes we may make to our privacy policy in the future will be posted on this page. You should check this page from time to time and take note of any changes.
